# HireLoop — Production AI Job Application Agent

## What This Is
HireLoop is a production-grade AI job application agent. It ingests user documents,
runs a multi-agent LLM pipeline, and auto-fills job applications using browser automation.
Every decision should be production-quality — not prototype quality.

## Non-Negotiable Principles
1. TypeScript strict mode everywhere — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
2. All LLM calls traced via Langfuse — every call must have a trace
3. All user data (CVs, personal info) is PII — never log, never expose, RLS on all tables
4. Never submit an application without explicit user confirmation
5. Generated content must only reference skills present in user's own documents
6. Every async function must handle errors — no unhandled promise rejections
7. Stream everything — never block the UI waiting for full LLM completion

## Architecture
- Frontend + API: Next.js 15 App Router (TypeScript)
- Agent framework: LangGraph.js (stateful multi-agent graph)
- RAG: Voyage AI embeddings → Pinecone → Cohere rerank
- Document parsing: LlamaParse
- Background jobs: Trigger.dev v3
- Browser automation: Stagehand (AI-native Playwright)
- Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage + RLS)
- ORM: Drizzle ORM
- Observability: Langfuse + Sentry

